WEBVTT

00:00:00.898 --> 00:00:21.351
So glad to be here with you and man, it's so heavy to think about how just two weeks ago I was in Sacramento and it was the galvanization of many pregnancy centers in California and they're all coming together and saying, hey, these are some things that we're fighting for.

00:00:21.391 --> 00:00:22.373
Here's what's true.

00:00:23.074 --> 00:00:28.242
And what I was marked with was the idea of what does legacy mean?

00:00:28.674 --> 00:00:35.901
And for me, I grew up without a dad and my dad was in that small town that I lived in.

00:00:35.961 --> 00:00:37.722
And I knew what he looked like.

00:00:38.383 --> 00:00:39.464
I knew what he drove.

00:00:40.005 --> 00:00:45.910
I knew that he was a husband and a father, but not to my mom and not a father to me.

00:00:45.950 --> 00:00:50.775
And the complexity of not understanding what's going on around you.

00:00:51.816 --> 00:00:53.517
Something that doesn't make sense to you.

00:00:53.838 --> 00:00:55.159
You have to make sense of it.

00:00:55.639 --> 00:00:58.642
And the way that I made sense of it is it must be my fault.

00:00:59.522 --> 00:01:04.148
And I thought that would make me impossible.

00:01:04.849 --> 00:01:08.093
It would be impossible for me to be a father, a husband, a contributor.

00:01:08.153 --> 00:01:10.196
And what does it even mean to be a man?

00:01:10.777 --> 00:01:18.247
And then later in life, when God blessed me with the opportunity to have a wife and to have four sons, seven, five, four and two.

00:01:18.267 --> 00:01:20.129
So, you know, praise God.

00:01:23.354 --> 00:01:26.738
And when I think about what does it mean to be a father?

00:01:28.162 --> 00:01:29.644
Like, how do you do that?

00:01:31.265 --> 00:01:35.130
Do I need to make enough, build enough so they have enough?

00:01:35.750 --> 00:01:36.691
Because that's what I thought.

00:01:36.891 --> 00:01:38.193
That was my testimony.

00:01:38.293 --> 00:01:48.424
I thought that if I earned enough, became enough, won enough, achieved enough, got enough applause, status stuff, and all the things.

00:01:48.744 --> 00:01:52.468
I thought if I had that, then I would feel as if I was enough.

00:01:53.449 --> 00:01:57.714
And I could believe the same thing as a dad.

00:01:58.402 --> 00:02:06.891
my wife taught me was that the greatest gift that I could give her and the greatest gift that I could give them is my presence.

00:02:08.252 --> 00:02:09.793
And yeah, praise God for that.

00:02:13.217 --> 00:02:26.290
So what I preached about and as I had the honor of, I don't even want to say, how could I even fathom

00:02:26.786 --> 00:02:38.763
speaking about or stepping into what Charlie was going to say, but what I was marked with was that idea of legacy, and legacy is not what you leave behind for someone.

00:02:39.184 --> 00:02:46.254
Legacy is what you leave within someone, and when you leave something within someone, it compels you to do something that's bigger than you.

00:02:47.556 --> 00:02:54.226
And that's the message that I brought, and that's the message that God has given me as a dad.

00:02:54.562 --> 00:03:06.339
what am I going to deposit in them so that it compels them to do, imagine more than God could ever, that we could ever hope, dream or imagine.

00:03:06.640 --> 00:03:10.345
And it's in their relationship with Jesus Christ at the end of the day.

00:03:10.425 --> 00:03:15.673
But for today, I want to dive into this text, Genesis 32.

00:03:17.055 --> 00:03:18.898
And we're gonna be in 22,

00:03:18.978 --> 00:03:20.460
Verses 22 through 32.

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:26.467
And it's this very interesting passage of scripture.

00:03:26.487 --> 00:03:33.195
And just to get to this point, I'm gonna just kinda give us a recap.

00:03:33.215 --> 00:03:37.820
But before we read the word of God, I just wanna pray really quickly.

00:03:38.561 --> 00:03:43.026
Heavenly Father, I thank you that you're good.

00:03:43.842 --> 00:03:52.673
And Lord, I just pray that your word, as it says in Hebrews 412, that we know that your word is like a double edged sword.

00:03:52.893 --> 00:03:55.216
It divides bone and marrow, soul and spirit.

00:03:55.236 --> 00:04:02.525
So God, I just pray that your word, it confronts the sin in us, that it compels us to love you deeper.

00:04:03.446 --> 00:04:06.029
Lord, I pray that it brings the forefront of our mind.

00:04:06.971 --> 00:04:12.978
Where is it in our life that we have created idols that stopping us from loving you in the way that

00:04:13.666 --> 00:04:15.268
You deserve to be loved.

00:04:16.670 --> 00:04:19.815
Search us, Lord, and we thank you for your word that is true.

00:04:20.556 --> 00:04:21.558
In Jesus' name we pray.

00:04:22.219 --> 00:04:22.539
Amen.

