00:06:04.546 --> 00:06:06.629
In this world, we will face tribulation.

00:06:06.649 --> 00:06:08.552
He's speaking to his disciples.

00:06:08.613 --> 00:06:11.557
He's not speaking to people who are far from Jesus.

00:06:11.898 --> 00:06:15.744
He's speaking people who are close to him, followers of Jesus.

00:06:15.764 --> 00:06:24.618
He's saying in this world, you will face calamity and trials and challenges and frustrations and you will fail people and people will fail you.

00:06:25.019 --> 00:06:31.890
In spite of that, you can face persecution and trials with a different perspective.

00:06:32.834 --> 00:06:40.662
not because the pain isn't real, not because the frustration isn't real, you can have a different perspective because the battle is won.

00:06:43.025 --> 00:06:48.231
And that's challenging and it's not something that's momentary, it's something to cling on to.

00:06:49.552 --> 00:06:58.802
And we see in this text specifically, Jacob has brought a lot of trouble on himself to get to this point

00:06:59.362 --> 00:07:03.551
where I'm about to read with Jacob, he's wrestling with God.

00:07:03.631 --> 00:07:06.457
I think it was better said, God wrestling with him.

00:07:06.477 --> 00:07:09.403
A lot has transpired in his life.

00:07:09.904 --> 00:07:16.978
He was born and he was holding on to his brother Esau's heel and that's something that,

00:07:17.186 --> 00:07:19.409
to define him, that's why he was named that.

00:07:20.891 --> 00:07:35.932
Jacob, it points to him being a backstabber, a deceiver, and we see that later on in his life, Esau, he comes home hungry, he's starving, and Jacob has this stew, this soup, and he's eating it.

00:07:36.373 --> 00:07:38.596
And Esau, he's like, man, give me some of that.

00:07:39.257 --> 00:07:45.746
And he sacrifices his birthright for soup, which is crazy.

00:07:46.818 --> 00:07:49.362
I hope that the soup was good, you know?

00:07:50.404 --> 00:07:57.436
But he sacrifices his soup for his birthright, this covenantal promise and all that has access to.

00:07:57.476 --> 00:08:04.228
And then later on he wants his father's blessing and he manipulates his father into giving him his blessing.

00:08:04.849 --> 00:08:12.722
His father, he was close to Esau and he tells Esau to go out and to go out into the fields

00:08:12.770 --> 00:08:20.604
and find a lamb or a goat and bring it back and prepare it in the way in which he loves and then serve it to him.

00:08:21.025 --> 00:08:31.743
And then Jacob and his mother, they conspired to rob this blessing that Isaac was going to give to Esau.

00:08:31.763 --> 00:08:33.266
And the way that they did that was,

00:08:33.890 --> 00:08:38.279
his mom said, hey, go out and get a few goats, and I'll prepare them.

00:08:38.299 --> 00:08:47.378
I know what he likes, I know how to season, I know how to cook it up, and he's gonna like it, and it's gonna be amazing, but I want you to put on your brother's clothes.

00:08:47.426 --> 00:08:49.508
The Bible's full of interesting details.

00:08:50.849 --> 00:08:54.673
So I guess Esau was a hairy man and Jacob was not.

00:08:55.514 --> 00:09:16.274
So to make sure that when his father who was very sick, his eyesight was very poor, to make sure that he can masquerade himself as Esau, he even put animal skin on his hands and his arms and on the back of his neck so that when he went close to his father and embraced him, he smelled like, felt like, and maybe even looked like

00:09:16.450 --> 00:09:17.411
someone who he wasn't.

00:09:18.492 --> 00:09:21.495
And this is the definition of Jacob.

00:09:21.575 --> 00:09:28.202
Jacob was so uncomfortable in his own skin, he thought he could force God's hand to giving him what he wanted.

00:09:28.522 --> 00:09:39.893
He thought he could create this life that was good enough so he felt like he had the blessing that he deserved but at the end of the day, ultimately, he did not trust God.

00:09:41.475 --> 00:09:44.818
And when we don't trust God and we try to

00:09:45.186 --> 00:09:46.849
create a life on our own.

00:09:46.869 --> 00:09:59.670
When we try to maintain our own autonomy, when we think that we are the best Lord over ourselves and we do things our way, it's never gonna go like we hope.

00:10:00.752 --> 00:10:01.754
And this is what we see.

00:10:02.355 --> 00:10:06.221
And then we get to Genesis 32.

00:10:07.483 --> 00:10:09.106
So that night,

00:10:09.410 --> 00:10:15.957
Jacob got up and took his two wives, his two female servants and his 11 sons and crossed the Ford of the Jabbak.

00:10:16.217 --> 00:10:20.642
So the Jabbak is the intersection of the Sea of Galilee and the Dead Sea.

00:10:20.963 --> 00:10:26.088
And it's this, you know, this really small stream and they're crossing there.

00:10:27.009 --> 00:10:32.855
And as they cross, after he had sent them across the stream, he sent over all his possessions.

00:10:33.296 --> 00:10:35.098
So Jacob was left alone.

00:10:35.598 --> 00:10:38.962
And a man wrestled with him until daybreak.

00:10:39.810 --> 00:10:47.020
When the man saw that he could not overpower him, he touched the socket of Jacob's hip so that the hip was wrenched as he wrestled with the man.

00:10:47.260 --> 00:10:51.786
Then the man said, let me go for it is daybreak.

00:10:51.806 --> 00:10:55.791
But Jacob replied, I will not let you go unless you bless me.

00:10:56.532 --> 00:10:58.896
The man asked him, what is your name?

00:10:59.957 --> 00:11:01.739
Jacob, he answered.

00:11:02.340 --> 00:11:06.706
And then the man said, your name will no longer be Jacob, but Israel.

00:11:07.298 --> 00:11:11.745
because you have struggled with God and with humans and overcome.

00:11:12.607 --> 00:11:16.493
Jacob said, please tell me your name, but he replied, why do you ask me my name?

00:11:16.533 --> 00:11:18.116
And then he blessed him there.

00:11:18.977 --> 00:11:28.934
So Jacob called the place, Paniel, saying it was because I saw God face to face, and yet my life was spared.

00:11:29.535 --> 00:11:34.002
The sun rose above him as he passed, Paniel, and he was limping because of his hip.

00:11:34.242 --> 00:11:42.555
Therefore, to this day, Israelites do not eat the tendon attached to the socket of the hip because the socket of Jacob's hip was touched near the tendon.

00:11:43.937 --> 00:11:46.782
And I just want to say, man, this is, this is wild.

00:11:47.202 --> 00:11:50.427
Like anyone that says that the Bible was boring, man, what are you reading?

00:11:51.689 --> 00:11:52.791
Like this is incredible.

00:11:52.871 --> 00:11:57.659
What a, what a, just so much going on in there.

00:11:58.200 --> 00:11:59.762
And again, so,

00:12:00.002 --> 00:12:02.126
All that had transpired that we talked about.

00:12:02.166 --> 00:12:05.391
So Jacob had tried to manifest his own destiny.

00:12:05.491 --> 00:12:10.480
He had stole his brother's Esau's birthright because he traded it for soup.

00:12:10.520 --> 00:12:12.523
And then he tricked his dad.

00:12:13.064 --> 00:12:23.762
And when Esau came back with the very thing that his dad asked him to come back with, he said, hey, I've already given the blessing away.

00:12:23.906 --> 00:12:27.011
was enraged and he vowed to kill his brother.

00:12:27.051 --> 00:12:36.847
And then since that moment, Jacob had been running and he'd been running for 20 years up until this moment that all of a sudden he finds out that Esau is coming.

00:12:37.588 --> 00:12:41.654
And not only is he coming, he's home with 400 men and he's terrified.

00:12:42.496 --> 00:12:45.861
And Jacob does what he does best, runs.

00:12:47.544 --> 00:12:48.185
He runs.

00:12:50.589 --> 00:12:51.410
But I love that

00:12:52.098 --> 00:13:00.129
we see in the text, God loved him enough to stop him from running so he could give him something that he could not catch on his own.

00:13:01.571 --> 00:13:07.559
And some of us, we're gonna be invited into wrestling with, what is it that we keep running away from?

00:13:09.021 --> 00:13:14.208
What is it that God has confronted yet we've turned our cheek to it?

00:13:14.669 --> 00:13:21.458
What has God invited us into stepping into but we feel like we're disqualified, it's too much, you're asking too much.

00:13:22.114 --> 00:13:33.834
Have you ever been in a place where you felt like you heard from God, but what God was asking you, that's too much, that's too big, that's too hard, it's too difficult.

00:13:34.656 --> 00:13:37.040
I don't wanna do that.

00:13:37.060 --> 00:13:47.378
I know that's been true in my life where my wife and I, we used to operate gyms before I was in ministry full time, and in the midst of that, we,

00:13:48.066 --> 00:13:57.639
We were like, man, I really feel God's call into full-time ministry and I stepped on staff at a church and it's been incredible ever since.

00:13:57.799 --> 00:14:06.851
But in the middle of that, in that transition, I grew up living in, I hate to say poverty, I've seen real poverty.

00:14:07.212 --> 00:14:09.635
But I grew up with not as much as most people.

00:14:10.876 --> 00:14:18.066
So the fact that my wife and I, we had bought our first home and we had our first child and everything looked

00:14:18.370 --> 00:14:18.770
Good.

00:14:18.810 --> 00:14:25.078
And we step into ministry and it was going to cost a lot of sacrifices.

00:14:25.778 --> 00:14:38.473
And I thought, well, okay, I'm stepping on staff at this position as an associate pastor and our income's gonna be cut into thirds, but at least we'll have this passive income from these gyms.

00:14:39.234 --> 00:14:43.218
And God said, that guy you've been pouring into,

00:14:43.842 --> 00:14:44.783
this man named Trevor.

00:14:45.424 --> 00:14:46.646
You've been discipling him.

00:14:47.287 --> 00:14:48.970
You've been elevating his leadership.

00:14:49.531 --> 00:14:50.653
You've been a good friend to him.

00:14:50.673 --> 00:14:52.436
I want you to give him the gym.

00:14:52.656 --> 00:14:58.305
I feel like I misunderstood what you said.

00:15:01.049 --> 00:15:09.382
Maybe you said you want me to give him part of it or give him a raise.

00:15:10.564 --> 00:15:11.826
Now I want you to give it away.

00:15:12.578 --> 00:15:18.404
I was like, but God, you know, but we still own this business loan.

00:15:19.265 --> 00:15:21.767
You know, we, this doesn't make sense.

00:15:22.328 --> 00:15:33.780
How are we supposed to, I thought that my wife was going to stay at home, you know, with the kids and I was going to do this and we did it anyway.

00:15:33.800 --> 00:15:34.520
And we gave it away.

00:15:35.061 --> 00:15:39.986
And in the middle of that season, so that was in June,

00:15:40.898 --> 00:15:51.531
that that happened and then December comes around and we're paying on the business loan and we get something in the mail in December and it looks like a check.

00:15:51.891 --> 00:15:53.553
I'm like, that looks like our check.

00:15:53.794 --> 00:15:54.374
That's not good.

00:15:54.975 --> 00:15:56.117
It looks like a return check.

00:15:56.177 --> 00:15:58.620
I'm like, man, what happened?

00:15:59.140 --> 00:16:05.608
And I opened it up and they were returning the check because someone had paid our balance in full.

00:16:05.628 --> 00:16:07.090
Yeah, yeah.

00:16:09.666 --> 00:16:11.248
And I was like, okay, gosh.

00:16:11.308 --> 00:16:30.091
And I think faith is like a muscle in that every time that you step out in faith and God does something that exceeds your imagination, what it does is it creates resilience in you to do something that's more difficult or greater or give more.

00:16:30.611 --> 00:16:36.178
Maybe it's radical generosity or maybe it's pouring your life into someone else.

00:16:36.290 --> 00:16:48.446
But I think time after time, when we think about this idea of reciprocity, it's like, man, when you step into what God is calling you to do, it's gonna be better than you think.

00:16:48.947 --> 00:16:50.028
It's always gonna be better than you think.

00:16:50.609 --> 00:16:55.356
I love this Hudson Taylor quote, I have it in my office.

00:16:56.036 --> 00:17:06.130
He was an early missionary and it says that God's plans, God's way will never let God's provision.

00:17:07.650 --> 00:17:10.095
So if he called you to it, he's gonna see you through it.

00:17:11.077 --> 00:17:20.475
And I think what Jacob is gonna see here is that he thinks he's gotta figure it out.

00:17:21.136 --> 00:17:28.210
He thinks he's gotta figure it out because we see in the early part of the text, so verses 22 through 24,

00:17:29.026 --> 00:17:43.904
That night Jacob got up and he took his two wives and his two female servants and 11 sons and he had daughters but they're not listed here but that everybody is crossing the fort of the Jabbak and he had sent them across the stream and he sent over all his possessions so Jacob was left alone.

00:17:46.027 --> 00:17:52.254
So he sends everything ahead, his family, his wealth, his security, everything that he's built and all of a sudden he's alone.

00:17:52.314 --> 00:17:55.538
And I just want you to understand the significance of this moment

00:17:58.242 --> 00:17:59.343
because God doesn't shout.

00:18:03.008 --> 00:18:18.708
And sometimes in our busy life, we need to quiet our minds because sometimes our own voice and our own narrative and our own set of preconceived notions has gotten in the way of God's voice.

00:18:18.908 --> 00:18:20.230
He hasn't stopped speaking.

00:18:20.470 --> 00:18:22.092
