00:19:48.477 --> 00:19:49.138
Think about that.

00:19:50.850 --> 00:20:03.594
We think we can manipulate or yes, we can petition unto God, we can worship God and in the moment of worship, like God meets us there, but we need to understand that God is never far away from us.

00:20:05.136 --> 00:20:09.184
The Bible tells us that he will never leave us or forsake us.

00:20:09.204 --> 00:20:14.674
But there's sometimes this perception that he's far away and often it's equated to shame or frustration.

00:20:14.754 --> 00:20:36.739
And when we think that God isn't moving at the pace that he should, or didn't do the thing that we think he ought to do, or maybe we've done something, and that shame, it impacts the way that we see God and see ourselves, we have this falsified idea that God is somewhere way over there.

00:20:36.759 --> 00:20:42.706
But he's actually right in the middle of our mess.

00:20:43.394 --> 00:20:47.200
And God loves him so much, he initiates the fight.

00:20:47.982 --> 00:20:52.709
And it's just a setup for this encounter.

00:20:54.192 --> 00:20:56.936
