00:40:07.749 --> 00:40:10.993
And we see that Jacob had spent his entire life trying to write his own story.

00:40:11.894 --> 00:40:14.877
And he had tried to make himself, he was a self-made man.

00:40:14.937 --> 00:40:20.242
But every version of that man had become

00:40:20.322 --> 00:40:28.330
a dead end but God says that name is finished, that story is over, I'm giving you a new name.

00:40:30.792 --> 00:40:31.193
Israel.

00:40:32.254 --> 00:40:35.257
Not because he earned it, because God gave it.

00:40:37.839 --> 00:40:41.503
And I'm just reminded of John 21.

00:40:41.683 --> 00:40:48.690
I think Michael was talking about this as well where Peter, he did the thing he said he would never do.

00:40:50.434 --> 00:40:51.576
I would never deny you Jesus.

00:40:52.738 --> 00:40:53.579
I would never do that.

00:40:55.302 --> 00:40:55.762
I would never.

00:40:57.786 --> 00:40:58.327
And he does it.

00:40:59.468 --> 00:41:01.071
Not once, not twice, but three times.

00:41:05.097 --> 00:41:15.634
And when Jesus restores him, when Jesus is cooking breakfast on this beach, he asks Peter, do you love me?

00:41:17.794 --> 00:41:22.941
Love, when we say love in English, it has a, you know, I can say I love doughnuts, I love my wife and children.

00:41:23.422 --> 00:41:24.483
Different, right?

00:41:24.844 --> 00:41:27.027
Different.

00:41:27.047 --> 00:41:33.656
So in Greek, different words, very distinct meaning.

00:41:34.037 --> 00:41:37.281
So Jesus says, do you agape me?

00:41:37.321 --> 00:41:43.330
The totality of love, this emptied out sacrificial love.

00:41:43.370 --> 00:41:44.852
Do you love me like that?

00:41:45.773 --> 00:41:46.514
Peter's like, no.

00:41:47.490 --> 00:41:48.831
I can't commit to that, I blew it.

00:41:51.033 --> 00:41:54.817
I flail you, I love you like a brother, but I can't commit to that.

00:41:55.278 --> 00:41:57.219
Jesus asked him again, second time, do you love me?

00:41:57.239 --> 00:41:58.080
Do you agape me?

00:41:58.561 --> 00:41:59.422
No, I can't commit to that.

00:41:59.922 --> 00:42:00.823
I love you like a brother.

00:42:01.083 --> 00:42:03.506
Third time he asked him, well, do you even flail me?

00:42:03.546 --> 00:42:05.327
And Peter was hurt.

00:42:05.347 --> 00:42:06.589
He was grieved in his spirit.

00:42:06.609 --> 00:42:09.311
He said, you know all things, Lord, you know that I love you.

00:42:12.214 --> 00:42:13.515
And then what does Jesus say?

00:42:14.356 --> 00:42:16.338
Does Jesus say, man,

00:42:16.706 --> 00:42:18.269
You're a great fisherman.

00:42:18.990 --> 00:42:20.152
You went back to fishing.

00:42:20.693 --> 00:42:21.554
This is what you're good at.

00:42:21.574 --> 00:42:22.516
That's your identity.

00:42:24.159 --> 00:42:27.284
That's what you decided you wanted to do.

00:42:27.324 --> 00:42:28.807
This is who you are, right?

00:42:29.328 --> 00:42:30.810
So go back fishing.

00:42:32.493 --> 00:42:32.673
No.

00:42:35.599 --> 00:42:42.290
You don't get to define you and you can't out send what Jesus has called you to do.

00:42:43.010 --> 00:42:43.932
Because he created you.

00:42:43.952 --> 00:42:47.237
He says, go feed my sheep.

00:42:49.762 --> 00:42:50.062
Why?

00:42:52.487 --> 00:42:53.528
Because that's who you are.

00:42:55.171 --> 00:42:58.838
He redefined him in spite of him.

00:42:58.858 --> 00:43:00.300
And this was, we see with Jacob.

00:43:00.360 --> 00:43:03.025
And Jacob was left different forever.

00:43:03.245 --> 00:43:08.274
We only see one more time in the totality of scripture where he's referred to as Jacob.

00:43:10.306 --> 00:43:15.826
If something was left behind and we have to see what the crescendo, the story, what happens?

00:43:16.489 --> 00:43:17.874
What happens next?

00:43:18.690 --> 00:43:22.693
Well, in Genesis 33 verse four, we see what happens when Esau finally gets there.

00:43:22.994 --> 00:43:31.541
After Jacob tried to manipulate the situation, he sent ahead these caravans of animals and money and all this stuff.

00:43:31.801 --> 00:43:33.903
He's sending Esau all this stuff.

00:43:33.943 --> 00:43:35.224
Maybe he'll spare my life.

00:43:35.264 --> 00:43:36.706
Maybe he'll have mercy on me.

00:43:36.926 --> 00:43:38.147
And he's sending these gifts.

00:43:38.427 --> 00:43:43.071
And then as he gets closer, as he approaches him, he bows seven times.

00:43:43.391 --> 00:43:48.676
And it's interesting to see that Jacob had tried to manifest a blessing so that people would bow

00:43:48.656 --> 00:43:53.665
Yet he found himself bowing to Esau seven times, seven folds.

00:43:53.705 --> 00:43:55.629
He returned this blessing in a different way.

00:43:55.910 --> 00:44:04.185
And as he approaches him, as death is getting close to him, as what he think, maybe the worst thing possible could happen, this is what transpires.

00:44:05.908 --> 00:44:11.058
The moment that he ran from, the moment that he prepared for, the moment that he tried to outmaneuver.

00:44:12.578 --> 00:44:21.770
Esau ran to meet Jacob and embraced him and threw his arms around his neck and kissed him and he wept.

00:44:21.790 --> 00:44:23.012
We need to understand.

00:44:23.052 --> 00:44:30.722
If we misunderstand the character of God, we'll misunderstand what God's word is telling us.

00:44:32.064 --> 00:44:35.489
I love thinking about the prodigal son.

00:44:39.895 --> 00:44:42.418
This father standing on a porch

00:44:43.458 --> 00:44:47.213
Maybe waving his finger, say, I knew you would blow it.

00:44:47.996 --> 00:44:48.739
You did it again.

00:44:48.759 --> 00:44:50.386
I told you so.

00:44:50.978 --> 00:45:07.833
Maybe when we have a broken human experience, we superimpose that and we put that on God and we think that, well, if we didn't do it in time or we're frustrated with God because we're not as far along as we thought we should be and we get overwhelmed and we feel like God is angry at us.

00:45:08.113 --> 00:45:10.515
So we distance ourselves from Him.

00:45:10.575 --> 00:45:11.676
We don't serve Him.

00:45:11.736 --> 00:45:12.777
We don't worship Him.

00:45:12.817 --> 00:45:13.738
We don't pray for Him.

00:45:13.798 --> 00:45:14.859
We don't read His word.

00:45:15.059 --> 00:45:17.721
We don't do what He says because we feel like we've done too much.

00:45:17.941 --> 00:45:20.964
We've gone too far because there's a father standing on the porch.

00:45:20.944 --> 00:45:24.662
and saying, hey, I told you from, you're not welcome here anymore.

00:45:26.250 --> 00:45:27.858
But the story tells us something different.

00:45:28.898 --> 00:45:34.903
that when his son who had blown his wealth, he asked for his inheritance early and he blew it and he's in a pigsty.

00:45:35.103 --> 00:45:37.325
And he's looking around, he's like, what have I done with my life?

00:45:38.206 --> 00:45:42.590
I know that my father, he takes care of his servants better than this.

00:45:42.810 --> 00:45:44.111
Maybe you'll let me work for him.

00:45:44.411 --> 00:45:47.574
And he starts making his way towards the father.

00:45:47.614 --> 00:45:51.698
And when he does, the father sees him and he doesn't wag his finger.

00:45:51.978 --> 00:45:53.099
He doesn't shut the door.

00:45:53.359 --> 00:45:54.400
He runs to him.

00:45:54.660 --> 00:45:58.884
And we have a good father in heaven that what he does, he puts a ringer.

00:45:58.864 --> 00:46:05.611
He puts a ring on his finger and a robe on his back and sandals on his feet and he throws a party because this is my son who's come home.

00:46:08.634 --> 00:46:09.795
That's who God is.

00:46:09.835 --> 00:46:19.085
So maybe he's patiently waiting for you to come home.

00:46:20.306 --> 00:46:24.210
Maybe he's patiently waiting for you to keep praying.

00:46:26.212 --> 00:46:28.114
Maybe the wrestle is that

00:46:28.898 --> 00:46:37.968
The prodigal son or daughter that hasn't yet come home, the most powerful thing you could do is petition God Almighty to do what you cannot.

00:46:41.191 --> 00:46:44.175
Maybe he wants to give you the strength to do something you can't do on your own.

00:46:45.236 --> 00:46:49.580
Or maybe he's asking you to let go of something you've been holding on to.

00:46:50.501 --> 00:46:58.450
Maybe something that's harboring anger in your heart or guilt or maybe it's an apology that you need to extend.

00:46:58.786 --> 00:47:01.049
Because unforgiveness, you know who it impacts most?

00:47:02.671 --> 00:47:02.771
Us.

00:47:04.854 --> 00:47:05.855
There's something.

00:47:05.916 --> 00:47:12.464
Anytime that we open this word, what happens is God's gift to us is conviction.

00:47:15.328 --> 00:47:19.394
May we not leave this room unchanged.

00:47:22.738 --> 00:47:25.762
Maybe there's something that's happened in our life that we have never shared with another person.

00:47:27.845 --> 00:47:28.626
Something that you've done.

00:47:29.250 --> 00:47:33.516
You confess unto God, first John says that we confess unto God, he's righteous and just, forgive us.

00:47:34.577 --> 00:47:41.827
But James 5.16 says that we need to confess to one another so that a righteous man can pray for us.

00:47:42.408 --> 00:47:46.234
Maybe a righteous sister can pray for us and then there can be healing.

00:47:46.834 --> 00:47:49.658
Maybe we're forgiven but we're still wounded.

00:47:50.139 --> 00:47:55.146
And an unhealed person, you might be forgiven but you still feel broken.

00:47:55.526 --> 00:47:58.130
And maybe that's the reason you keep going back to the thing that

00:47:58.434 --> 00:47:59.638
You said you would never do it again.

00:48:01.764 --> 00:48:05.596
Maybe today's the day you draw the line in the sand and say, hey, the buck stops here.

00:48:06.620 --> 00:48:09.970
Not because of me, but because of God.
